-- Qatar May Set Up $1 Billion Investment Company, QNA Reports
-- B y   R o b e r t   T u t t l e
-- 2012-02-16T05:18:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-16/qatar-may-set-up-1-billion-investment-company-qna-reports.html
Qatar’s Supreme Council for Economic
Affairs and Investment considered a proposal to set up a $1
billion company that would invest in small enterprises outside
the country, the state-run Qatar News Agency reported yesterday,
citing Finance Minister Yousef Kamal.  The question of bringing state energy company  Qatar
Petroleum  under the council’s authority was also considered, the
agency said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Robert Tuttle  in Doha at 
 rtuttle@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
